---
---

<section id="cli" class="relative overflow-hidden bg-[var(--color-phantom)] py-24 text-white md:py-32">
  <div class="absolute -right-40 top-0 h-[600px] w-[600px] rounded-full bg-[var(--color-brand-purple)] opacity-25 blur-[180px]" aria-hidden="true"></div>
  <div class="absolute -left-40 bottom-0 h-[400px] w-[400px] rounded-full bg-[var(--color-brand-blue)] opacity-15 blur-[160px]" aria-hidden="true"></div>

  <div class="container-x relative grid items-center gap-12 lg:grid-cols-[1.15fr_1fr] lg:gap-20">
    <div>
      <div class="eyebrow-purple">
        <span class="inline-block h-1.5 w-1.5 rounded-full bg-[var(--color-brand-purple)]"></span>
        The unique differentiator
      </div>
      <h2 class="h-section mt-5 text-white">
        Your team uses Claude Code and Codex?
        <span class="block text-[var(--color-brand-purple)]">We're the only DLP that sees them.</span>
      </h2>
      <p class="body-lg mt-6 max-w-[560px] !text-[var(--color-steel)]">
        Browser DLP solves chatbots. But AI now runs through CLI agents that talk straight to vendor APIs.
        Tracehold ships an endpoint agent for <span class="font-semibold text-white">Windows, macOS and Linux</span>
        that inspects AI egress on the device, before your data ever leaves the machine.
      </p>

      <div class="mt-8 grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-2">
        <div class="surface-card-dark !p-5">
          <p class="text-[12px] font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.14em] text-[var(--color-brand-blue)]">Built for CLI AI</p>
          <p class="mt-2 text-[14px] leading-snug text-white">
            Coverage of terminal AI agents that most DLP tools simply don't have.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="surface-card-dark !p-5">
          <p class="text-[12px] font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.14em] text-[var(--color-brand-blue)]">DORA-ready</p>
          <p class="mt-2 text-[14px] leading-snug text-white">
            Treats AI vendors as third-party ICT risk, with hard evidence of egress controls.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <a href="/#demo" class="mt-10 inline-flex items-center gap-2 rounded-full bg-white px-5 py-3 text-sm font-semibold text-[var(--color-phantom)] transition hover:bg-[var(--color-brand-purple)] hover:text-white">
        Book a developer-team PoC
        <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true">
          <path d="M5 12h14M13 5l7 7-7 7"/>
        </svg>
      </a>
    </div>

    <div class="relative">
      <div class="overflow-hidden rounded-2xl border border-white/10 bg-black/40 shadow-2xl backdrop-blur">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-2 border-b border-white/10 px-4 py-3">
          <span class="h-2.5 w-2.5 rounded-full bg-[#ff5f57]"></span>
          <span class="h-2.5 w-2.5 rounded-full bg-[#febc2e]"></span>
          <span class="h-2.5 w-2.5 rounded-full bg-[#28c840]"></span>
          <span class="ml-3 font-mono text-[11px] text-[var(--color-steel)]">~/proprietary-app · claude code</span>
        </div>
        <div class="space-y-2 p-6 font-mono text-[12.5px] leading-relaxed">
          <p class="text-[var(--color-steel)]"><span class="text-[var(--color-brand-blue)]">$</span> claude "refactor auth.ts and explain"</p>
          <p class="text-[var(--color-graphite)]">→ reading src/auth.ts (482 lines)</p>
          <p class="text-[var(--color-graphite)]">→ sending to api.anthropic.com…</p>
          <div class="mt-3 rounded-md border border-[var(--color-brand-purple)]/40 bg-[var(--color-brand-purple)]/10 p-3">
            <p class="text-[var(--color-brand-purple)]">⚠ tracehold: egress intercepted</p>
            <p class="mt-1.5 text-white">detected: <span class="text-[var(--color-brand-blue)]">AWS_SECRET_KEY</span> in auth.ts:142</p>
            <p class="text-white">detected: <span class="text-[var(--color-brand-blue)]">internal_db_host</span> in auth.ts:18</p>
            <p class="mt-2 text-[var(--color-danger)]">policy: BLOCK · stopped on the device before it left the machine</p>
          </div>
          <p class="text-[var(--color-graphite)]">→ event logged · org=acme · severity=critical</p>
          <p class="text-[var(--color-brand-blue)]">$ <span class="animate-pulse">▍</span></p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
